    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>II. SIGNAL CONDITIONER</title>
        <para>It conditions the input signals for the internal microprocessor
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1450111">1.11</hotlnk>.
            </emph>
            This enables the microprocessor to interpret the signals.
            <emph type="bold"></emph>
            Signal conditioning usually consists of converting analog signals to digital signals, squaring up sinewave
            signals or amplifying low intensity signals to a level the ECM microprocessor can process.
        </para>
        <figure id="ef1450111" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg1100" filename="../figeg1/eg1100.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 1.11 - Electronic Control Module Signal Conditioning</caption>
